The paper discusses methods for extending the functionality of blockchain-enforced smart contracts, which involves topics related to cryptography (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), software engineering (cs.SE), deep learning (cs.DL), and databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions potential applications in various domains such as legal, medical, financial, government, and IoT, which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories.
